# Project: 1Chat SDK — A Chat SDK for 1chat.xyz with Rust

1Chat SDK is a SDK for 1chat.xyz, this sdk will be used to build chat bot, integrate with OpenClaw, HermesAgent for 1chat.xyz, the app will be used to chat with the users, group of 1chat.xyz.

1Chat API/Stream communication
- They're using protobuf to define their API & call their API via gPRC-Web
- For API call, call via gRPC-Web
- To receive message from 1Chat, they're using gRPC Stream 1 way from 1Chat server to client only.

Features that 1Chat SDK need to support
- Receive message via Stream
- Send message via gRPC Web via Direct Message, Group Message
- Send file, image, video, audio, document to Direct Message, Group Message
- React Emoji to a message via gRPC Web

We need to research on how to generate the Rust code from the protobuf file, and how to call the API via gRPC-Web in Rust (check this link: https://github.com/grpc/grpc-web)

The parameters to setup a bot is BOT_TOKEN & TENANT_ID & API_1CHAT_URL (check @.env.local for testing)
THE API_1CHAT_URL is the URL of Envoy Gateway already, we just need to call the API via gRPC-Web, don't need to cover the proxy part.

We have two references that you can use to get some sample codes:
 - Python, it isn't written in SDK style, they write for integrate with Hermes Agent: @reference/python
 - Typescript, it is written in SDK style, they write for integrate with Open Claw: @reference/typescript

This project need to write in the style of SDK, very easy to use, and Agent friendly, we can give the repo to agent & they know how to integrate with 1Chat via our SDK

## Deployment

When a PR is merged to `main`, M7 adds GitHub Actions to build and `cargo publish` to [crates.io](https://crates.io) (secret `CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN`; local copy may live in `.env.local` — never commit it). Versions follow [semver](https://semver.org/).

## Layout

- `src/` — SDK library (`onechat_sdk`)
- `proto/` — protobuf sources (`myconversation/api/…`) plus vendored `google/api` and `validate`
- `build.rs` — `tonic-build` client codegen
- `reference/` — local-only TypeScript/Python samples (gitignored; do not push)
- `.cursor/plans/2_roadmap.md` — milestones M0–M7

## Workflow

Proto → Rust: edit files under `proto/`, then `cargo clean -p onechat-sdk && cargo build` (requires `protoc`). See `AGENTS.md` for commands and the agent-friendly API target. Package name is `onechat-sdk` (Cargo forbids leading digits; product name remains 1Chat).